ped since the event.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 10. Jan 2022) 0aPhilosophical anthropology. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Anthropology / Cultural & Social.2bisacsh  aTanner Lectures.  aThe Tanner Lectures.  aanthropology.  aaspiration.  abehaviour.  aethnography.  ahuman condition.  ainterest.  aphilosophy.1 aAnderson, Elizabeth, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLear, Jonathan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aOrtner, Sherry B., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRobbins, Joel, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Toronto Press Complete eBook-Package 2021z978311073922040uhttps://doi.org/10.3138/978148753959740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781487539597423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781487539597/original  a978-3-11-073922-0  University of Toronto Press Complete eBook-Package 2021b2021  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_SN  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK